✨ New launch alert! ✨
HEYTEA’s Triple Supreme Matcha Latte drops on July 10 — and here’s the best part: it’s Buy 1 Get 1 Free on launch day only 💚

But wait, there’s more — for just $1.99, you can take home their Matcha Cloud, freeze it, and make your own ultra-rich matcha ice cream 🥹✨
No fancy machine needed. Just your freezer and a spoon🫧

Honestly, this might be your new favorite summer dessert. 💚

#HEYTEA #HEYTEAUSA #MatchaCloud #TripleSupremeMatcha #lamatcha #matchaicecream

✨ DIY milk tea bingsu at home? YES! 🍧

Tried something fun with @mrbrowncoffeeus ’s Brown Sugar Milk Tea — it’s made with Vietnamese black tea, creamy New Zealand milk, and real brown sugar with a soft caramel touch 🤎

I froze it in cute shell molds, added injeolmi powder, mochi & condensed milk for that Korean dessert vibe!

So simple, so refreshing, and honestly… kinda addictive 🧊🫶

If you love milk tea, this one’s a must-try. 🤍

🚨 Costco New Drop Alert!

Just found Jinbo Collection’s Sichuan Dan Dan Noodles — and wow, this one’s a must-try.
It comes with a rich sesame sauce and chili oil infused with Sichuan peppercorns.
No meat, but seriously bold flavor. It’s nutty, spicy, and gives you that real Sichuan-style heat. ❤️‍🔥✨
Each box has 10 packs for $17.79, and it’s available at select Costco locations in LA, Bay Area, Seattle, and now Texas!
I was lucky to grab one — some LA locations are already selling out, so don’t wait too long.
Tastes just like something you’d get at a restaurant — and you can easily make it at home with your own toppings.
If you’re into Dan Dan noodles, don’t skip this.

@jinbo_collection ❤️‍🔥❤️‍🔥

If you haven’t tried King Yubu yet, here’s your sign.
They’ve got 22 different yubu pockets, each with unique flavors and toppings—so choosing just a few feels like a mini adventure. 🥢 From spicy to savory to sweet, the variety is wild.
And if you go for lunch, they’ve got an amazing deal: any 3 yubu + 1 soft drink for just $14.99! 👀
We also tried their mala rosé tteokbokki—and trust me, this one stands out.
There’s also tons of other options like cupbop, hand roll, loaded fries, and even dessert drinks.
 Everything is super affordable, and the portions are generous. 👍🏼✨✨✨
Perfect for a quick lunch, a casual dinner! 

@kingyubu_la 
📍3128 W 8th St, Los Angeles, CA 90005

How to get $10 at In-N-Out 🍔 (yes, really)

Step 1: Go to the App Store and download an app called Claim
 Step 2: Sign up and use my code ELLIE10 — that’s the only way you’ll unlock the $10 reward for In-N-Out!
 Step 3: Most important part: link the credit/debit card you use the most AND your Venmo. If you skip this step, you won’t get your cashback. Seriously, don’t skip it!

After that, just go to In-N-Out and pay with your linked card. You don’t have to show anything, click anything, or scan anything. Just pay like normal.
Claim will automatically track your purchase and send you $10 through Venmo — usually within a few days. I used my Chase card and got my cash the very next day. My friend used another card and it took about 3 days. So it depends on the card, but it works!
How easy is that? 🍟💵

—

So what is Claim?

@claim_co 
 It’s a cashback app that pays you to eat at places you already love — no receipts, no scanning, no weird steps. Just link your card, claim a weekly reward, and eat.
Claim is available in: Atlanta, Austin, Boston, Chicago, Dallas-Fort Worth, Houston, Los Angeles, New York, Philadelphia, and Washington, D.C.
Some of the brand options include: In-N-Out, Chipotle, Dunkin’, Starbucks, Wingstop, Blue Bottle, Crumbl Cookies, and more. (Brands vary by city!)
New rewards drop every Thursday, and you get to pick one each week.
Download Claim and use code ELLIE10 to start saving 💸

Guess the Pot! Eat for Free? ❤️‍🔥
Can you guess the weight of your hot pot?

@bigway.hotpot just opened in Rowland Heights, and they’ve got over 80 ingredients to choose from! You build your own bowl — pick what you want, choose a flavor and spice level, and they cook it fresh for you. They have vegan options too!

They offer both regular hot pot and dry hot pot, and you can even add cheese or rice.

There’s also a DIY sauce bar, tons of drink options, and yes — free ice cream at the end.

⭐️Ellie’s picks: the Szechuan Green Pepper Broth and the Spicy Szechuan Dry Mix — both were my favorites! They weren’t too spicy on their own, so I went with the spiciest level, and it was perfect for me. ✨

@bigway.hotpot 
📍18904 Gale Ave, Rowland Heights, CA 91748

#BigWayLA #DIYHotpot #BigWayHotPot

Did I just step into Seoul?! 🇰🇷
This weekend (June 21–22, 2–6PM), head to Seoul Stop on the 2nd floor of Source Mall in Buena Park for their K-beauty pop-up event—and trust me, you don’t wanna miss this.

Here’s what’s happening:
1️⃣ First 500 guests get a free K-beauty goodie bag 
2️⃣ Spend $50+ and get a surprise Braye bag 🎁
3️⃣ Spend $100+ and score a $50 gift 💸
4️⃣ Spend $30+ and you can join the Medicube raffle ✨

There are tons of other freebie events too—so go early, have fun, and don’t leave empty-handed!

They’ve got all your favorite K-beauty brands in one place, with testers available so you can actually try before you buy. I picked up a bunch of stuff I’ve been eyeing for ages!

And don’t skip the snacks—this place feels like a real Korean convenience store.
Instant ramen, viral Korean drinks, kimbap, chips… grab a few and thank me later 🍜🧃

@seoul_stop 
@thesourceoc 

📍6988 Beach Blvd Unit B-215, Buena Park, CA 90621

#kbeauty #seoulstop #thesource

Seafood lovers, this one’s for you. 🦞
This $159 all-you-can-eat seafood buffet is inside Hilton Universal, right next to Universal Studios.
The highlight? Unlimited Maine lobsters and king crab legs — plus snow crab legs, shrimp cocktail, oysters, mussels, and more. 🥹
The seafood selection is huge and super fresh.
They’ve also got a chef making pasta to order,
a full hand roll sushi bar, and tons of hot dishes like steak, lamb, prime rib, duck, and dim sum. ❤️‍🔥
And don’t sleep on dessert —
two types of chocolate fondue, boba, donuts, cakes, ice cream… endless choices.
Drinks are unlimited too — wine, beer, and mimosas are all included. 🍻🍷🍹
Perfect spot for a special weekend dinner.
Parking is validated, and they also offer brunch on Saturdays and Sundays for $109 per adult. 💓

@cafesierrahilton 
📍555 Universal Hollywood Dr, Universal City
